4 HJR___ COMMENDING PAUL H. REYNOLDS FOR HIS LONG-STANDING
5 PUBLIC SERVICE.
6
7 WHEREAS, highest commendations are herein proudly
8 presented to Paul H. Reynolds for outstanding public
9 service; he has devoted many decades to political and civic
10 engagement, playing a significant role in the development
11 and growth of the Republican Party in Alabama; and
12 WHEREAS, his involvement in politics began in 1964
13 while attending college, when he worked for a conservative
14 radio station in Hattiesburg, Mississippi, and participated
15 in the presidential campaign of United States Senator Barry
16 Goldwater; and
17 WHEREAS, over the years, Mr. Reynolds has been
18 actively involved in numerous political campaigns and party
19 leadership roles, including supporting Congressman Bill
20 Dickinson's campaigns, directing the Gerald Ford
21 presidential campaign in several Alabama counties in 1976,
22 and assisting with regional efforts supporting President
23 Ronald Reagan and United States Senator Jeremiah Denton in
24 1980; and
25 WHEREAS, in 1974, he was elected to represent Butler
26 County on the Alabama Republican Party State Executive
27 Committee, where he served faithfully until 1998, providing
28 leadership and helping guide the party through decades of
Page 1

leadership and helping guide the party through decades of
HJR209 INTRODUCED
29 growth and development; and
30 WHEREAS, Mr. Reynolds later served as Chair of
31 Alabama's Second Congressional District for the Alabama
32 Republican Party from 1998 to 2008 and, in 2008, was elected
33 Alabama's National Committeeman to the Republican National
34 Committee, where he contributed to national policy
35 discussions and party leadership; and
36 WHEREAS, among his notable initiatives, Mr. Reynolds
37 helped lay the groundwork for the national "Keep Nine"
38 effort, advocating for a constitutional amendment to
39 maintain the traditional nine-justice structure of the
40 United States Supreme Court; and
41 WHEREAS, Paul H. Reynolds' decades of leadership,
42 dedication, and steadfast commitment to public service have
43 had a lasting and meaningful impact on Alabama's political
44 community and on the many individuals with whom he has
45 worked over the years; now therefore,
46 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
47 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That Paul H. Reynolds is highly
48 honored and commended for his distinguished service to the
49 State of Alabama, and this resolution is offered to him in
50 deepest admiration and appreciation for his immeasurable
51 service, as well as with sincere best wishes for continued
52 success in all future endeavors.
